From: johnsonfarmsus
Subject: [PATCH] ml/device: sort GPU devices purely by free memory

The default ByFreeMemory.Less function unconditionally ranks integrated GPUs
as "less than" discrete GPUs, regardless of free memory. After sort.Reverse(),
this means discrete GPUs are always preferred — which is wrong on systems
where the iGPU has more usable memory than the dGPU, and especially wrong
where the dGPU is an unsupported ROCm arch (e.g. RDNA1 alongside a Phoenix
iGPU on a Ryzen 7040/8040 series box).

Sort purely by FreeMemory so the device with more headroom wins, regardless
of integrated-vs-discrete classification.

---
 ml/device.go | 5 -----
 1 file changed, 5 deletions(-)

diff --git a/ml/device.go b/ml/device.go
--- a/ml/device.go
+++ b/ml/device.go
@@ -365,11 +365,6 @@ type ByFreeMemory []DeviceInfo
 func (a ByFreeMemory) Len() int      { return len(a) }
 func (a ByFreeMemory) Swap(i, j int) { a[i], a[j] = a[j], a[i] }
 func (a ByFreeMemory) Less(i, j int) bool {
-	if a[i].Integrated && !a[j].Integrated {
-		return true
-	} else if !a[i].Integrated && a[j].Integrated {
-		return false
-	}
 	return a[i].FreeMemory < a[j].FreeMemory
 }

